verbose_text: Experimental studies indicate that the alterations of fatty acid (FA) as constituents of membrane phospholipids have been implicated in the pathogenesis of hypertension by competing for eicosanoid metabolic pathway to change the balance of vasodilator / vasoconstrictor, the systemic arterial compliance mediated by the release of nitric oxide (NO), 3 and the voltage dependent L-type Ca 2+ channel levels.
